title: Yearbook 2005 Jan Van Eyck dot type
content:
Does anyone recognize this typeface? Or know of something similar?

Thanks in advance,  
Jeremy

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20081015201431im_/http:/www.typophile.com/files/yearbook_6496.png)

 [‹ Possible custom?](http://web.archive.org/web/20081015201431/http:/www.typophile.com/node/42820 "Go to previous forum topic") [Does anyone know what font this is?? ›](http://web.archive.org/web/20081015201431/http:/www.typophile.com/node/42818 "Go to next forum topic")
author: jeremyl

comments.content: What’s the source? James Goggin created something similar for the Tate. [Frieze](http://web.archive.org/web/20081015201431/http:/www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/club_21/frieze_ot/) is similar.

Thanks! I’ll take a look at Frieze. The source is a catalog for the Jan Van Eyck school. I think the typeface is something called Pinball or Pinball Rond. I can’t find any info on it.

Best,  
Jeremy
